Sentencas: Nanocrystalline strontium doped lanthanum manganite (La0.65Sr0.3MnO3) having variable particulate sizes and morphology is synthesized by a novel spray pyrolysis (SP) technique for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) cathode.
Titulo: Synthesis of nanocrystalline lanthanum manganite with tailored particulate size and morphology using a novel spray pyrolysis technique for application as the functional solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: Precalcined nanopowders received from the first SP run are added as the seeding agent in the subsequent runs for their in-situ growth inside the reactor.
Titulo: Synthesis of nanocrystalline lanthanum manganite with tailored particulate size and morphology using a novel spray pyrolysis technique for application as the functional solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: The suitability of the nano and micro particulates having interconnected porosity are examined as cathode functional and current collection layers.
Titulo: Synthesis of nanocrystalline lanthanum manganite with tailored particulate size and morphology using a novel spray pyrolysis technique for application as the functional solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: Detailed physical, microstructural and bulk electrical characterizations of such nanopowders are studied.
Titulo: Synthesis of nanocrystalline lanthanum manganite with tailored particulate size and morphology using a novel spray pyrolysis technique for application as the functional solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: Cathode polarization behavior and the associated rate limiting steps are characterized using AC impedance spectroscopy in the symmetric cell configurations.
Titulo: Synthesis of nanocrystalline lanthanum manganite with tailored particulate size and morphology using a novel spray pyrolysis technique for application as the functional solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: The optimization of the cathode processing conditions has brought the interfacial polarization down to similar to 0.2 Omega-cm(2) and thereby increases the cell performance from 2.0 to 3.2 A.cm(-2) (0.7 V, 800 degrees C).
Titulo: Synthesis of nanocrystalline lanthanum manganite with tailored particulate size and morphology using a novel spray pyrolysis technique for application as the functional solid oxide fuel cell cathode

Sentencas: Such improvement in anode-supported SOFC is correlated with the cathode processing conditions, particulate size, morphology and cathode microstructure.
Titulo: Synthesis of nanocrystalline lanthanum manganite with tailored particulate size and morphology using a novel spray pyrolysis technique for application as the functional solid oxide fuel cell cathode
